x4freetext: Lab. de Chimie Nucleaire.

x4codes.shortRef: Jour: Journal of Inorganic and Nuclear Chemistry, Vol.36, p.495 (1974)

x4freetext: In French.
-Mass distributions in fission of U-238 by 14 MeV
neutrons -.
The Melusine reactor at the Laboratory was
used for the U-235 measurement.
Sames Accelerator for the U-238 measurement.
Reactor neutrons with a fast (En>1 MeV) to
thermal flux ratio of about 0.01 was used for the
U-235 measurement.
The Sames Accelerator produced a 300 keV
deuterium beam on a tritium target for the U-238
measurements.
Flux of 10**13 n/cm**2/sec .
-Uranyl nitrate in a sealed polythene sachet, enriched
to 93 % in U-235 ( (1-5)*10**-05 g) for thermal
fission measurements.
-Natural uranium oxide UO3 in a sealed polythene sachet
for the U-238 14 MeV measurements. 1-5 g weight.
-For the krypton data uranyl stearate prepared by the
technique of Wahl+ was used.
Decay gamma measurement after chemical
separation of fission products.
.Three chemically separated fractions were studied,
alkalis with alkali earths and rare earths, a fraction
with cadmium and silver, and a fraction with krypton
and xenon, and a fraction with iodine.
Two coaxial Ge(Li) detectors, 43 and 50
cm*3, with resolution of 2.3 and 2.5 keV at 1.332 MeV
peak of Co-60.
.Values are weighted averages of many independent
measurements.
Tables 2 and 3, JIN,36,495.
Changes in main BIB-section and DECAY-DATA
in SUBWORK 002.
M.M. BIB information was added.
Dates were corrected for 4-digits year.
Free text was corrected to be human-readable.
Misprints were corrected.
FACILITY, INC-SOURCE, INC-SPECT, SAMPLE lines were
moved in respective Subents.

x4code.headerHelp: Error in value of quantity, defined under ERR-ANALYS

x4freetext: Quoted uncertainty is from a quadratic
combination of errors on several independent
measurements. This comes from four sources: the area
of gamma peaks, the efficiency of the detector,
the uncertainty in timing and nuclear decay data.
Cumulative thermal fission yields.
The Melusine reactor at the Laboratory was
used for the U-235 measurement.
Reactor neutrons with a fast (En>1 MeV) to
thermal flux ratio of about 0.01 was used for the
U-235 measurement.
Flux of 10**13 n/cm**2/sec .
-Uranyl nitrate in a sealed polythene sachet, enriched
to 93 % in U-235 ( (1-5)*10**-05 g) for thermal
fission measurements.

as 6.34 PC/FIS.
